00:12:24.027 --> 00:12:31.797
proving that the planet you live on isn’t a ball, it isn’t round, but a flat pancake?

00:12:32.937 --> 00:12:38.277
YouTube, after all, is a business that exists to make money, the

00:12:38.277 --> 00:12:42.157
longer it can keep a user on the website, the more money it makes.

00:12:42.757 --> 00:12:47.677
Flat earth videos were very good at keeping users on the website, so

00:12:47.877 --> 00:12:52.097
YouTube had a strong incentive to recommend Flat Earth videos to people.

00:12:53.437 --> 00:12:59.357
Secondly, and on a related note, the fact that these videos were so popular

00:12:59.657 --> 00:13:03.597
meant that people knew that they could make money by creating new videos

00:13:03.627 --> 00:13:07.557
about them, even if they didn’t believe the flat earth theory themselves.

00:13:08.937 --> 00:13:12.477
People saw how many views other flat earth videos were getting

00:13:12.777 --> 00:13:16.587
and thought, well, I’ll create one too and get in on the action.

00:13:17.207 --> 00:13:21.937
So, it wasn’t just the YouTube algorithms that were pushing users to the

00:13:21.937 --> 00:13:27.157
videos, real people were making more flat earth explainer videos in order

00:13:27.157 --> 00:13:30.807
to profit from the interest that they knew there was in the subject.

00:13:32.237 --> 00:13:37.737
The end result was, as you might imagine, lots of people being suggested Flat

00:13:37.737 --> 00:13:41.427
Earth videos, which were excellent at converting new people to the movement.

